// examples/Q/q_failure on linearity violation.ds
// Q-Regime Example 7: Failure on linearity violation
//
// Demonstrates a *hard* linearity violation that MUST be rejected by the compiler.
// This example is intentionally non-compiling and is fully commented out.
//
// Purpose:
//  - Reinforces that linearity violations are detected statically.
//  - Shows that no runtime failure or effect is possible because the program
//    is invalid and must not be executed.
//
// This example differs from "invalid copy" by showing *implicit discard*
// rather than explicit duplication.

